### ðŸªœ Steps to Solve

1. Open your terminal and type the following command to log into the remote server using SSH:

    ```bash
    ssh bandit0@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
    ```

2. When prompted, enter the password:

    ```
    bandit0
    ```

3. Once logged in successfully, youâ€™ll see a welcome message and the terminal prompt will change to something like:

    ```
    bandit0@bandit:~$
    ```

